  "comments": "Progress continues toward a robust TLS-inspecting proxy path. Updated the Squid ACL to replace the placeholder allow-list with a more concrete set of destinations. Remaining gaps include validating SSL bump configuration across clients, fully enforcing proxy adoption on all internal hosts, and conducting a controlled re-run of the attack to verify exfil blocked with logged evidence. Next steps should also include distributing the CA trust to all endpoints, expanding and testing the allow-list, and ensuring comprehensive proxy logs are collected for audit and validation.",
